classDiagram
    class Task {
        +str title
        +int duration_minutes
        +str priority
        +str preferred_time
        +str notes
        +priority_value() int
    }

    class Pet {
        +str name
        +str species
        +int age
        +str special_needs
        +species_emoji() str
    }

    class Owner {
        +str name
        +str available_start
        +str available_end
        +str preferences
        +available_minutes() int
    }

    class ScheduledTask {
        +Task task
        +str start_time
        +str end_time
        +str reason
    }

    class Scheduler {
        +Owner owner
        +Pet pet
        +List~Task~ tasks # may use heapq(Priority Queue) - this would give me 0(log n) priority sorting vs (
        +build_schedule() tuple
        +_explain(task, start_time) str
    }

    Owner "1" --> "1..*" Pet : owns
    Scheduler --> Owner : uses
    Scheduler --> Pet : plans for
    Scheduler --> "0..*" Task : schedules
    Scheduler --> "0..*" ScheduledTask : produces
    ScheduledTask --> Task : wraps
